rComments: She is a wonderful Professor. She is always ready to help students and answer questions. Her assignments require significant effort and are more take-home exams than typical assignments you'll find in other courses. This weighs out the fact that there was no final exam for this course. Definitely recommended.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Accessible outside class', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: The one professor after 21 years, I recall as being one of the best I had during my time at Rutgers.  I can say it was inspirational as it really has made me thing about things over the years in different ways to solve different problems in CS Research and Development that I've applied professionally.  She kept it fun and thought provoking.

I had this prof for a seminar on how children learn language. The material is not what I expected it to be and it was pretty hard to comprehend. The course was set up in a way that in first term there was an assignment or essay almost weekly. Suzanne is an ok prof - she makes herself available for help after class which is really helpful

She may look like a hippie because of the long hair, but she teaches really well. Just go to lectures, follow along, and you're set. The assignments are a bit too long though. You really have to earn your 3%!
NICE LADY. LOOKS LIKE A HIPPIE.
